	   <tr><td colspan=2>Alright I was stuck a little while with this but I went around destroying every MOB in the area until I found, and then I felt stupid because it was so easy.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Lord Elgnub information is correct, he spawns in the spike room in Blackburrow after you have kept all commanders, splitpaw gnolls, and elite guards in the zone killed.  Then with the gnoll high shaman pops in the green room, kill that too.<br><br>The two spawns in Splitpaw from the entrance are as follows, you will need invis and/or levitate to get out.<br><br>One Eye Gnoll:  Come from the entrance, go down the hall to the double doors, through the single door and on the bridge where you can jump down, do so (you'll take roughly 60 to 30dmg) then proceed through the door that you can see from there.  You are now looking at a campfire and either a Tesch Gnoll or the one eye.  This is where to pick up the gnoll eye.<br><br>From there go to Scribe spawn...<br><br>Gnoll Scribe:  Go out the door you just entered, do not go up that ramp next to the fire because this just leads to deeper into zone.  Out of the door you just entered, turn left and at the next intersection you can open a left door or go right.  Proceed right, and do not go up the stairsin the next room.  There is a room on the opposite back left corner of hte room you just entered with the scribe and a lleth val gnoll or two lleth val gnolls.  The Scribe will spawn as the left MOB.  Try to root or snare it as you do have 4 MOBs back to the one eye gnoll spawn that you might not want to bother with.<br><br><br>As for charges, a level 51 Paladin is able to use them.  ;p  Good luck with this everyone, it's been two long years of wanting to do this, and I've finally finished it.  And damn was it easy.  Ha!<br><br>Dunraven Steelblizzard<br>51 Nameless Pally<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
